This paper focuses on the analysis of user behavior in interactive information retrieval, specifically in the context of academic search engines. The paper discusses the usage of search stratagems and their impact on the search process performance. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), and Cybernetics (cs.CY). However, given the focus on information retrieval and user behavior, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.HC and cs.CL.
